  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Postnatal - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_postnatal">Postnatal</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_postnatal">Postnatal</xref>
 is the period of time immediately after childbirth, and is defined for the baby.         </p>
    <p>
For the 
              <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_maternity_services_data_set">Maternity Services Data Set</xref>
 the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_postnatal">Postnatal</xref>
 period will end either following the baby's discharge from 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_maternity_service">Maternity Services</xref>
 or discharge from a 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation" keyref="supporting_definition_neonatal_unit">Neonatal Unit</xref>, whichever is later.        </p>
    <p>
Note: 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_postpartum">Postpartum</xref>
 is for the mother.        </p>
  </div>
